result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael L Ingram was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Michael L Ingram in court with attorney Aaron M. Damrau.  Defendant Michael L Ingram in custody.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 16CM163, 16CT35, 17CF93 and 17CF152 @ 9:12 a.m. State advises no joint recommendation, will be asking for PSI, Def free to argue. Response by Atty Damrau. Recess 9:14. Resume 9:15. State advises both sides will argue and presents what each side will be arguing. Response by Atty Damrau. Recess 9:22. Resume 9:31. State has not changed position. Atty Damrau clarifies what will be arguing for. Def understands and wishes to proceed. Court reviews plea quest. forms with Def. 17CF93 ct 1 - no contest plea. 16CT35 ct 1 - no contest plea. 17CF152 ct 1 - no contest plea. Ct 2 - no contest plea. 16CM163 ct 1 - no contest plea. Court grants motion to dismiss and read in 17CF93 cts 2 & 3, 17CF152 cts 3 & 4, 16CM163 cts 2 & 3. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Damrau satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds Def guilty of 17CF93 ct 1, 16CT35 ct 1, 17CF152 cts 1 & 2, and 16CM163 ct 1. State presents sentencing arguments. State advises Def has credit for 142 days on 17CF152, 8 days in 17CF93, and 1 day in 16CM163. Atty Damrau gives sentencing arguments. Believes 17CF152 credit is 143 days. State will agree to that as DOC will advise if incorrect. Brief statement by Defendant. Court asks Def questions and gives sentencing remarks. 
Orders on 17CF93 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, court costs, DNA surcharge and sample, credit for 8 days if revoked, AODA and follow through, abs. sobriety, no use or possession of controlled substances , med only as prescribed, counseling as required. Apply bond. 
16CT35 - 30 days jail, huber, $350 plus costs, 12 months revocation, retroactive to admin susp, alcohol assessment, no credit for time served. Jail is consecutive to any other sentence. Apply bond, then apply bond from 17CF93. Pmt plan if any balance due. 
17CF152 ct 1 - controlling sentence. Imposed and stayed prison 5 yrs, 30 months ic, 2 1/2 yrs es. 4 yrs probation, court costs, DNA surcharge, same conditions as 17CF93, credit for 143 days if revoked. Ct 2, withheld sentence 3 yrs probation, concurrent, same conditions, court costs, DNA surcharge waived on ct 2. 
16CM163 ct1 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, concurrent, court costs, DNA surcharge, credit for 1 day if revoked. Apply bond if any remaining from 17CF93 or 16CT35.
Jail to begin today if not already serving a sentence. Def eligible for CIP and SAP. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. 
 If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. 16CF163 State has complied with victim notification rights.
Plea/sentencing hearing on November 2, 2017 at 09:00 am.
